java.lang.Object

    • getChainAsArray

      public static Object[] getChainAsArray(Object startNode, String dataFieldNameArg, String nextFieldNameArg, Boolean circularChainArg, Boolean skipNullsArg)
      retrieve the contents of a chain, retaining the order of the entries
      Parameters:
      startNode - reference to the beginning of the chain
      dataFieldNameArg - name of the data reference
      nextFieldNameArg - name of the next reference
      circularChainArg - true indicates that the chain is expected to loop back on itself; false indicates that a loop is a corrupted chain
      skipNullsArg - true indicates that null data in the chain should be skipped; false indicates that null data should be included in the returned contents
      Returns:
      contents the data from the chain
      Since:
      1.7
